{{Year in Sri Lanka|1983}}

The following lists events that happened during '''1983 in [[Sri Lanka]]'''.

==Incumbents==
*[[President of Sri Lanka|President]]: [[J. R. Jayewardene]]

==Events==
* Following the ambush of a [[Four Four Bravo|Sri Lankan Army military patrol]], the [[Black July]] riots begin claiming the lives of over 1000 ethnic tamils. roughly 150,000 people were homeless with many businesses burnt.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=kGBBq-vmEyYC&pg=PA244#v=onepage&q&f=false Community, Gender and Violence, edited by Partha Chatterjee, Pradeep Jeganathan]</ref>
* The 2 decade long [[Sri Lankan Civil War]] begins on 23 July following ethnic tensions between the [[Sri Lankan Tamils|Tamil]] minority and the [[Sinhalese people|Sinhalese]] majority.<ref name="mod-defeat">{{cite news|title=LTTE defeated; Sri Lanka liberated from terror |date=18 May 2009 |url=http://www.defence.lk/new.asp?fname=20090518_10 |work=Ministry of Defence |accessdate=18 May 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090521113622/http://www.defence.lk/new.asp?fname=20090518_10 |archivedate=21 May 2009 |df= }}</ref>

