{{Year in Sri Lanka|1990}}

The following lists events that happened during '''[[1990]] in [[Sri Lanka]]'''.

==Incumbents==
*[[President of Sri Lanka|President]]: [[Ranasinghe Premadasa]]

==Events==
* On 11 June 1990, members of the [[Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam]], a were responsible for the [[1990 massacre of Sri Lankan Police officers|killing]] of over 600 unarmed Sri Lanka Police officers in Eastern Province, Sri Lanka.<ref name="lank1">{{cite web|url=http://www.lankanewspapers.com/news/2011/6/67843.html |title=Recalling the saddest day in Lankan Police history |accessdate=2011-06-12 |year=2011 |work=Lanka Newspapers |publisher=Lanka Newspapers |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110615103423/http://www.lankanewspapers.com/news/2011/6/67843.html |archivedate=2011-06-15 |df= }}</ref>
* Eelam war 2 begins following the attack the Sri Lankan government placed an embargo on food and medicine entering the [[Jaffna]] peninsula and the [[Sri Lankan Air force|air force]] relentlessly bombed LTTE targets in the area. The LTTE responded by attacking Sinhalese and [[Muslim]] villages and by massacring civilians. 


